<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-17T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="705" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.01/39: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Howard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-17T18:00:00-04:00">August 17, 1937—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>12. Your no. 23, August 17, 11 a.m. arrived too late to enable the
                            Department to give you instructions. Please report what took place at
                            the meeting this afternoon, which it is presumed in the absence of
                            specific instructions you did not attend.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>